00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:24.811
What Jesus has said,
he's not doing away with the

00:18:24.811 --> 00:18:27.190
Law here, he's
intensifying it.

00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:30.488
If it's hard not to commit
adultery, and believe me for a

00:18:30.488 --> 00:18:33.256
lot of people it is hard not to
commit adultery,

00:18:33.256 --> 00:18:35.200
it's even harder not to lust.
 

00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:38.068
If it's hard not to murder
someone,

00:18:38.068 --> 00:18:40.547
and if you knew some of the
people I have to work with

00:18:40.547 --> 00:18:43.538
around here you'd know that it
is hard not to murder someone,

00:18:43.538 --> 00:18:46.460
it's even harder not to be
angry with them.

00:18:46.460 --> 00:18:50.637
And if it's hard not to
retaliate when someone knocks

00:18:50.637 --> 00:18:55.618
you down, it's even harder to
let them knock you down again.

00:18:55.618 --> 00:18:59.511
Jesus is intensifying the
Jewish Torah and making it

00:18:59.511 --> 00:19:01.650
almost impossible to keep.
 

00:19:01.650 --> 00:19:05.690
But he's still expecting His
disciples to keep it.

00:19:05.690 --> 00:19:10.199
What Matthew presents Jesus is
doing is not getting rid,

00:19:10.199 --> 00:19:13.150
at all, of the Torah,
the Jewish law,

00:19:13.150 --> 00:19:15.200
he's intensifying it.
 

00:19:15.200 --> 00:19:18.170
There are a couple of places
where it sounds like Jesus is

00:19:18.170 --> 00:19:18.900
going again.
 

00:19:18.900 --> 00:19:29.442
You have a hand washing
incident, let's look at that,

00:19:29.442 --> 00:19:42.015
that's in chapter 15:17--well I
think I have to start reading a

00:19:42.015 --> 00:19:45.259
bit earlier.
 

00:19:53.809 --> 00:19:56.269
Where is it?
 

00:19:56.269 --> 00:19:57.769
Yeah, the very first part of
the chapter:

00:19:57.769 --> 00:20:00.189
The Pharisees and scribes came
to Jesus from Jerusalem and

00:20:00.189 --> 00:20:02.522
said, "Why do your
disciples break the tradition of

00:20:02.522 --> 00:20:03.160
the elders?
 

00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:05.210
For they do not wash their
hands before they eat."

00:20:05.210 --> 00:20:06.544
He answered them,
but why do you break the

00:20:06.544 --> 00:20:07.130
commandment ...?
 

00:20:07.130 --> 00:20:09.767
And He goes onto this sort of
thing and He basically says that

00:20:09.767 --> 00:20:11.843
they're not keeping the law
perfectly themselves,

00:20:11.843 --> 00:20:13.400
that they should keep it
better.

00:20:13.400 --> 00:20:16.906
Verse 10, "
He called the crowd to him and

00:20:16.906 --> 00:20:20.000
said to them,
"Listen and understand.

00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:22.557
It is not what goes into the
mouth that defiles a person,

00:20:22.557 --> 00:20:25.298
it is what comes out of the
mouth that defiles the person.

00:20:25.298 --> 00:20:28.828
Now in Mark's version of this
story, right around here,

00:20:28.828 --> 00:20:30.788
Mark adds a little sentence.
 

00:20:30.788 --> 00:20:33.188
Remember when I talked about
Mark, he gives you little clues

00:20:33.188 --> 00:20:35.098
that you're really supposed to
pay attention.

00:20:35.098 --> 00:20:38.476
Here Mark gives a little
parenthetical comment he says,

00:20:38.476 --> 00:20:41.288
"By saying this,
Jesus declared all foods

00:20:41.288 --> 00:20:42.288
clean."
 

00:20:42.288 --> 00:20:45.767
In other words,
Mark does a good little Gentile

00:20:45.767 --> 00:20:47.279
Christianity move.
 

00:20:47.279 --> 00:20:50.154
He takes this saying of Jesus
and he says, Jesus was declaring

00:20:50.154 --> 00:20:52.509
all foods clean so we don't have
to keep kosher.

00:20:52.509 --> 00:20:55.529
Matthew doesn't do that,
he saw that sentence in Mark,

00:20:55.529 --> 00:20:57.590
but you read this whole
chapter, that sentence which

00:20:57.590 --> 00:20:59.410
Matthew knew was in Mark is not
in Matthew.

00:20:59.410 --> 00:21:01.480
Matthew took that out.
 

00:21:01.480 --> 00:21:03.400
Why?
 

00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:06.778
Because he didn't want Jesus to
declare all foods clean;

00:21:06.778 --> 00:21:09.685
because in his Gospel Jesus
teaches that Christians have to

00:21:09.685 --> 00:21:11.038
continue keeping the Law.
 

00:21:11.038 --> 00:21:15.950
Matthew has Jesus disagree with
the scribes and Pharisees,

00:21:15.950 --> 00:21:18.390
but what he says here is that
it's much more important--

00:21:18.390 --> 00:21:20.845
sure, keeping kosher may be
important but it's much more

00:21:20.845 --> 00:21:23.390
important what's going on in
your heart and your mind,

00:21:23.390 --> 00:21:24.970
it's much more important what
you say.

00:21:24.970 --> 00:21:27.818
So Jesus spiritualizes in a way
or he--

00:21:27.818 --> 00:21:30.240
again he intensifies the law
and he's saying,

00:21:30.240 --> 00:21:33.253
yeah it's important to wash
your hands perhaps but that's

00:21:33.253 --> 00:21:34.170
not a big deal.
 

00:21:34.170 --> 00:21:37.125
It's important to pay attention
to the kosher but that's not a

00:21:37.125 --> 00:21:37.660
big deal.
 

00:21:37.660 --> 00:21:39.088
He makes it a moral lesson.
 

00:21:39.088 --> 00:21:41.279
That's not anti-Jewish,
that's not at all--

00:21:41.279 --> 00:21:43.824
you have all kinds of Hebrew
prophets in the Old Testament

00:21:43.824 --> 00:21:46.323
doing that kind of stuff all
over the place saying things

00:21:46.323 --> 00:21:48.009
like,
God doesn't want just your

00:21:48.009 --> 00:21:49.490
sacrifice he wants your heart.
 

00:21:49.490 --> 00:21:52.519
This is the way Jesus is
presented in Matthew as--

00:21:52.519 --> 00:21:56.258
just like a Jewish prophet,
an Israelite prophet who is

00:21:56.258 --> 00:21:59.261
intensifying the law,
giving it a moral teaching,

00:21:59.261 --> 00:22:01.750
but he never teaches anything
about giving it up.

00:22:09.068 --> 00:22:11.650
Jesus, though,
also besides being the one who

00:22:11.650 --> 00:22:14.420
teaches about Torah,
and He's being presented as

00:22:14.420 --> 00:22:17.154
Moses, and Matthew presents
Jesus more than any other

00:22:17.154 --> 00:22:19.259
Gospels as the founder of the
church.

00:22:19.259 --> 00:22:21.358
In fact, if you look for the
word "church"

00:22:21.358 --> 00:22:23.623
in some of the Gospels it's
very hard to find it because

00:22:23.623 --> 00:22:24.568
it's anachronistic.
 

00:22:24.568 --> 00:22:26.775
Jesus didn't go around in his
own life talking about the

00:22:26.775 --> 00:22:28.660
church, the church developed
after His death;

00:22:28.660 --> 00:22:32.230
Matthew retrojects the
conversation about the church,

00:22:32.230 --> 00:22:33.710
and even the foundation of the
church,

00:22:33.710 --> 00:22:36.650
and sort of laws about the
church into the mouth of Jesus.

00:22:36.650 --> 00:22:42.306
Look at 16:17,
and this is one we already read

00:22:42.306 --> 00:22:47.460
very carefully in Mark,
the same story.

